<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1st... what is your skill lvl?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I was the first 250 high elf smith on vaz without any modifier.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2nd... explain how i can make 8 / 11 bracers<br>
and then how i can make 1 / 25 pauldrons?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It's all about the RNG.  I am sure you'll see from time to time that you get 2/10 on boots and 9/10 on helm.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Some may trivial at 252, other pieces may trivial at 260 for all we know. VI have not given us the option to see beyond 250, the only information they have allowd us is.... &gt;250 &lt;-- must be hard then. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
That's why people who are interested on getting stuff make should always use the smith with max level (250 without mod right now, even SOE did say no skill can go beyond 252 with mod, that's for the person to decide).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>refer again to mistletoe sickles.... <br>
In 20 attempts, i create up to 5 sickles...<br>
compare that to crimson darkscale bracers/visors/gorgets and boots<br>
In 20 attempts, i create up to 16 items.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
My smith (high elf) has 250 skill without mod, when making sickles, she has 40% success rate.  Me, has 222 skill, when making sickles, I have 40% success rate.  Do you know why?<br>
<br>
It's all about the stats.  I have 355 wis + 305 all stats when buffed with focus.  My smith has 255 int and 255 str.  I am sure RNG likes to screw around from time to time, that's why my smith can normally make BP, Legs easy but when it comes to boots and pauldron is like hell.<br>
<br>
