<br>
As far as difficulty, I have noticed a huge variation in difficulty in the erudite cultural pieces.  3 swatch combines are much, much harder (I'm 250 tailoring).  Kuros (also a GM erudite) claims he has never failed a bracer (and done quite a few) yet he fails 75 percent of his robes, bp's, and legs.  The 3 swatch are definitely harder than the 2 and 1 swatch combines for erudite cultural, pretty much everyone I've talked to who does a lot of cultural says this.  I have a fairly large sample size and routinely stock about 40 different pieces of erudite cultural on my mule.<br>
<br>
Second, as far as success rate and stats, stats do not affect success rate.  Skill level (including effects from mod items) is the only factor that affects success rate (Absor posted this on the EQTraders forums).  Higher int, wis, or str (str only in the case of smithing) affect the rate at which you get skillups, but do not affect the chance of success on any item.  At one time in the past, wisdom affected succeses rate and intelligence affected the skillup rate, but this was changed quite some time ago (and was posted by a Verant representative on multiple forums).  Currently, skillup rate is determined by max (int, wis, str) for smithing and max (int, wis) for tailoring.<br>
<br>
Here's a link to EQTraders.  I can't find the original Absor post, but this post lists the official information received from Verant regarding stats and their effects on tradeskills.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=31">mboards.eqtraders.com/php...c.php?t=31</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Hope this info helps.<br>
